<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ghost1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ghost,</orth> subst. 1) the spirit of a deceased person: <bibl n="shak. mm 5.440" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 440</bibl>; cf. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.4.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 4, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.337" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 337</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.381" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 381</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 63</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.84" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.158" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 158</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.3.39" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 3, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.52" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.7.87" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.231" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 231</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.231" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 231</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.26" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.3.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 3, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 3, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.5.17" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 1, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.7.16" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 7, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.87" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.87" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 87</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.313" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 313</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.14.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 14, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.278" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 278</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.88" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.88" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 88</bibl><lb />2) a spirit in general, a supernatural being: <cit><quote>that affable familiar g. which nightly gulls him with intelligence,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 86.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 86, 9</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) a spectre: <cit><quote>grim-grinning g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 933" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 933</bibl></cit> (Death called so).
<lb />4) life, soul: <emph>to give up the g.</emph> (== to die) <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 1, 89</bibl>. <cit><quote>to yield the g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.67" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 67</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.37" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 37</bibl>.
<lb />5) a dead body: <cit><quote>a timely-parted g., of ashy semblance, meagre, pale and bloodless,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.161" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 161</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I'll make a g. of him that lets me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 85</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>